## Purpose
Allow users to "relocate" a missing project by selecting a new path via the folder browser. This preserves the project's ID and any associated data while updating where Maestro looks for it.

## Use Case
1. User moved `~/dev/my-project` to `~/dev/projects/my-project`
2. Maestro shows project as "Missing"
3. User clicks Relocate
4. Folder browser opens, navigated to `~/dev` (parent of old path, or default if parent gone)
5. User navigates to `~/dev/projects/my-project`
6. User clicks "Update Location"
7. Project is now tracked at new path, same ID preserved

## Why Preserve ID?
The project ID is a UUID used in routing (`/project/[id]`). By keeping the same ID:
- Bookmarks to the project still work
- Any future features using project ID (settings, history) stay linked
- Cleaner than delete + re-add

## Visual Design
The relocate dialog is similar to the add project modal, but:
- Different title: "Relocate Project" instead of "Select Project Folder"
- Shows the old path for context
- Button says "Update Location" instead of "Add Project"
- No custom name input (keep existing name)

